-- Miami Heat Beat Bulls as LeBron James Scores 35 in Playoff Rematch
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2012-01-30T05:04:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/miami-heat-beat-bulls-as-lebron-james-scores-35-in-playoff-rematch.html
LeBron James  had 35 points and 11
rebounds as the  Miami Heat  beat the Chicago Bulls 97-93 in a
rematch of teams that met in the  National Basketball
Association ’s Eastern Conference finals last season.  Chris Bosh  added 24 points and 12 rebounds for the Heat
(15-5) at AmericanAirlines Arena in Miami, while  Dwyane Wade  had
15 points on 4-of-16 shooting in his second game back from an
ankle injury.  Derrick Rose  scored 34 points to lead the Bulls (17-5), who
lost to Miami in five games in last season’s best-of-seven
Eastern Conference finals.  The  Dallas Mavericks  beat the San Antonio Spurs 101-100 in
overtime yesterday as  Jason Terry  scored 34 points.  Dirk
Nowitzki  returned for  Dallas  (13-8) after missing four games
with a knee injury and had 10 points and 13 rebounds.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  